sVnews
p4
VThe Carnatic music lovers of Walajapet were treated to an enjoyable vocal concert by Vasudha Kesav during the Rama Navami festival held at  Sri Veera Anjaneyar Temple in Walajapet on April 3.Vasudha began the concert with  the rendering of &#8216;Rama Namamu Brahma Rakshaka Mantram&#8217; of Tyagaraja in  Ataana, which was preceded by a soulful rendering of the sloka, &#8216;Ramaaya Rama Bhadraya.&#8217;Vasudha provided aural pleasure to the audience with her rendering of Tyagaraja&#8217;s &#8216;Brovabarama&#8217; in Bahudari, Arunachala Kavirayar&#8217;s &#8216;Ramanukku Mannan Mudi,&#8217;Dikshitar&#8217;s &#8216;Ramachandram Bavayami&#8217;  and Tyagaraja&#8217;s &#8216;Brochevarevarura&#8217; in Khamas and &#8216;Marugelara&#8217; in Jayantasri, the latter marked by ease and aplomb, showing her professional approach in understanding  the pulse of the audience.Charukesi, a very popular raga in Carnatic music, was taken up for raga elaboration by the artist, who did full justice to it by traversing through the octaves with felicity.S.P. Ananthapadmanabha&#8217;s version on the violin for the kriti was sweet and smooth.  &#8216;Kasturi Thilakam Lalata Palake,&#8217; a slokam in Yaman preceded &#8216;Bhavayami Gopala Balam&#8217; of Annamacharya in khanda chapu.Vasudha  rendered &#8216;Sara Sara Samarai&#8217; of Tyagaraja in Kuntalavarali and the sloka, &#8216;Kalyanadhbuda&#8217;  followed by Purandaradasa&#8217;s &#8216;Venkatachala Nilayam&#8217; in raga Sindhubhairavi. She rendered another sloka, &#8216;Manojavam Maruta Tulya Vekam&#8217; in praise of Lord Anjaneya in  Behag, followed by a rendering of &#8216;Hanumanmatave&#8217; of Purandaradasa. She concluded  the concert with a traditional mangalam of Saint Tyagaraja.Vasudha Kesav was accompanied on the mridangam by Mudra Bhaskar. C.S. Vijayaraghavan, honorary secretary of Amirthavarshani Sangeetha Sabha, welcomed the gathering.  Nalini Vijayakumar, vice president of the Sabha, proposed the  vote of thanks.
